  "text": "BCCIP protein was detectable in tumor formed in BCCIP-CKD;p53 −/− mice (Fig. 5d) , suggesting that the tumors may not be derived from BCCIP-deficient cells, when Trp53 was deleted. Loss of tumor suppressor activities of p53 itself in the progenitor cells of the mammary epithelium is sufficient to initiate a rapid neoplastic transformation [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . The same is true for skin cancers. This tumor development is so quick and penetrant that it may precede and completely mask tumor development driven by BCCIP deficiency, which is likely a slower and longer process. Thus, additional mouse models are needed to test the epispastic interactions between p53 and BCCIP in breast cancer.",
